Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Cut lengthways
into thin wedges.

Put the pepper wedges onto a #baking tray{} and drizzle with @oil{}. Season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until soft and slightly charred,
~{14-16%minutes}.

While the pepper chars, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #medium frying pan{}
on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{260%g}. Stir-fry until the
chicken is golden brown and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its
> packaging.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a
#garlic press{}).

Add the garlic and @peri peri seasoning{1%sachet} to the chicken. Fry for
~{1%minute}.

While the chicken cooks, trim the @baby gem lettuce{1}, halve lengthways,
then thinly slice.

Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}.

In a #small bowl{}, mix together the @mayonnaise{3%tbsp} and
@sweet chilli sauce{32%g}.

A couple of minutes before you're ready to serve, pop the
@plain taco tortillas{6} onto a baking tray and into the oven to warm through,
~{1-2%minutes}.

When everything's ready, lay the tortillas onto your #serving plates{}
(3 per person).

To make your tacos, spread the base of each with sweet chilli mayo,
top with the baby gem, charred pepper and peri peri chicken.

Finish with your grated cheese. Enjoy!